Slicin’ the 6 lb RibEye into Thick-cut Steaks. Smokin’ the family of RibEyes to 115 IT indirect with Natural Lump and Hickory Chunks.Searin’ the 2 lb RibEyes to 125 IT direct on the grill Large over Flammin’ Natural Lump🔥 Toppin’ with Fresh Parsley Chimichurri.Pairin’ the RibEyes with Grilled Veggie Kabobs and a Red-White-Blue Spinach Salad. RibEyes rubbed with Gaucho Steakhouse, Pink Himalayan Salt, Black Peppercorns, and binded with Olive Oil.... Veggie Kabobs seasoned with Garlic Herb and Pink Salt!💨🔥🥩

Miguel of @cooking_with_fire___ fires up some cheesy chimichurri quesadillas on the @nomadgrills. Marinate with chimichurri sauce (Miguel's recipe below) then sear for 4 minutes per side. Let rest for 5 minutes before slicing. Add cheese to your tortilla and top with heaps of meat. Garnish with cilantro, red onion, lemon juice, creamy chipotle sauce and enjoy.

= Chimichurri =
• 1 bunch flat leaf parsley
• 2 tsp oregano
• 4 minced garlic cloves
• 1 tsp chili flakes
• 1/4 cup red wine vinegar
• 1/2 cup olive oil

• Salt & pepper to taste

= Creamy Chipotle Sauce =
• 3 tbsp sour cream
• 1 tbsp chipotle
• 1 tsp cilantro
• Juice of 1/2 a lemon
• Salt & pepper to taste

The king of outdoor cooking, Max of @grillhunters, takes on the king of seafood on his @nomadgrills — melted with some garlic, herbs and lemon compound butter. Max's tribe is stoked for the smell of some smoked lobster in the air! 🦞🦞 #nomadgrills

= INGREDIENTS =
• 2 Live Lobster

= COMPOUND BUTTER =
• ½ cup butter softened
• 2 tbsp lemon juice
• 2 cloves garlic minced
• 1½ tbsp fresh chives chopped
• 1½ tbsp fresh rosemary chopped
• 1½ tbsp lemon zest
• ½ tsp kosher salt
• ½ tsp pepper

= INSTRUCTIONS =
• Fire up coals in a chimney.
• While the coals are heating up, mix all the compound butter in a small bowl.
• In the center of a plastic wrap, put the compound butter and wrap tightly both ends.
• Place in the refrigerator while prepping the lobster.
• Slice both lobsters lengthwise, inserting the knife between both eyes first to neutralize nervous system.
• Place your hot coals under the cooking grates.
• Melt about 2 tbsp of the compound butter and pour on the raw lobster meat.
• Place the half lobsters, meat down, on the smoking grates.
• After 5 minutes, turn the lobsters over, place a cube of compound butter on top and cook for another 3 minutes.

Reverse Sear Ribeye Steaks 🥩🔥 Too rare or Perfect for you?👇(Full recipe below)

1. Get yourself a thick steak and season with sea salt and black pep. This was a beautiful Galacian ribeye.
2. Leave uncovered in the fridge to brine ideally overnight, then rest at room temp for atleast an hour
3. Pat dry
4. Place steak in middle shelf of pre-heated 90•C fan oven 
5. Remove the steak when internal temp of meat hits approx 115f (medium-rare) - may take up to an hour
6. Pre-heat pan/skillet to max heat, then lace with beef fat or veg oil
7. Pat the beef dry, place it into the pan and don’t touch for 2 mins
8. Flip the steak to sear the other side, lower the heat a little and add 4tbsp unsalted butter, a couple cloves of garlic, thyme and Rosemary 
9. Baste the steak with the butter for another 2 mins, then from pan, pour over basting butter and rest
10. Slice against the grain, sprinkle with sea salt and serve with your sticky garlic cloves. ENJOY !

PRIME RIB DINNER🔥 Comment your favourite sides to eat with steak 🥩👇

Fries:
1. Cut 2 russet potatoes into fries then soak in cold water for at least 30 minutes
2. Drain and dry with towel
3. Fry at 300F for 8 minutes, then fry again at 375F until golden brown 

Rib roast:
1. Bring your roast up to room temp (will take over an hour depending on size)
2. Season with salt, pepper, garlic powder then sear on a hot pan on all sides until browned
3. Place in oven with vegetables at 300F until hits 130 internal or desired doneness. (2.6kg roast took  me about 2 hours)
4. Let it rest for at least 45 minutes before cutting. ENJOY !

60 Day Dry Aged Picanha (Covered in frosting?) 🥩

Up against any cut, the Picanha debatably comes out on top. IMO even against the ribeye! While slightly less tender, the Picanha is much more beefy (a trade-off I can get behind).

Why does all of this matter? Besides being something I recommend everyone try, Picanha is a cut that shines in the format of high graded Wagyu. Excessive marbling can be overwhelming on most cuts, but I find that Picanha’s beefiness makes it one of the few that can stand up to this richness.

Cheesy Taco Meat Filled Biscuits. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Add 1/2 pound of ground beef tot a medium high frying pan and cook until browned
- Add 1 small diced onion and 1 small diced poblano pepper and cook for about 5 minutes
- Drain the liquid, and add 1/4 cup of taco seasoning, 1/2 cup of beef stock and 1/2 cup of shredded cheese
- Add about 1 tablespoon of the meat mixture to each space of an ice cube tray 
- Place about a 1 inch piece of jack cheese in the center of the meat, and then another teaspoon of the meat mixture on top
- Freeze for 1 hour
- Flatten out a piece of biscuit dough and press in 1 tablespoon of the cheese
 - Place one of the meat cubes in the center and pinch the dough closed
